Alias Lien, Of course I do NOT trust you, so whatever you may have written, you can obviously re-write,and repost.  Be that as it may, let me tell you about me, and why I &quot;may&quot; harbor hostile feelings at you. (1) For 15 years I had a neighbor, a former Capt. in the RVN (South Viet Nam), and his wife and 4 kids. We were never really close but did exchange spring rolls for choc. chip cookies twice a year, and their kids came to me for advise, as their dad was too &quot;old fashioned&quot; to tell them about drugs and rock &amp; roll.  <br><br>
One day. with no warning, and out of the blue, he filed a million dollar lawsuit against me over a totally bogus property line issue.  That was after he had been sued by the Home Owner Association 14 times for CC&amp;R violations.  Why he choose to live in a &quot;planned&quot; community is beyond me.  What was obvious is that there were plenty of Good Old American White Boy Lawyers who liked the color of his cash, and filed a stupid and without merit lawsuit.  He wanted a million dollars for intentional infliction of emotional distress because I parked my ski boat next to my house and he could see it from a second story window (and he never had been to a doctor).  It was thrown out of court. By the time &quot;it&quot; was done, I was out abut 25 thousand dollars.  <br><br>
What I learned is that lawyers loved Vietnamese, Vietnamese loved to sue, and Vietnamese thought this was the American way.  Correct me if I am wrong. PLEASE!  It sure left a sour taste in my mouth.  Despite his unloading trucks in the dead of night, or stating in depositions that he had no source of income or ran no business, I never complained about him and his obviouslys illegal business ventures (my opinion). <br><br>
His kids have gone on to become attorneys and doctors, and I am as proud of them as if they were my own kids.  But, they are your generation.  He and I are the older generation.  I moved away, he is still there.  Does that shape my opinion? Oh, just a tad. He actually once tried to stab me over the fence with a tree saw, and I actually, to my horror in retrospect, got my shotgun out of the closet. So much for neighbors getting along. White, Asian, Black or whatever.<br><br>
I also do disabilty evaluations for a professional living, for state or county or federal aide, and I have seen 100's of Vietnamese wanting to get free &quot;American&quot; money.  I think 90% of them, at least were bull shit and I so wrote my opinion.  It was not there fault. REPEAT, I DO NOT THINK IT WAS THEIR FAULT. They were told this is the American way. <br><br>
You say you are sick and you get big dollars.  Well, I disagree.  Is this racist or realist? You be the judge, Lien, or who ever you are. Are your parents pulling in the dough, or are you?  Or any relative?  Or, like the majority of your community, are you sweating and working your collective asses off to make an honest days dollar, and telling the government, county, state, or federal, to take their &quot;free&quot; money and stuff it?<br><br>
Sorry to rain on your college parade, Lien, but do you know, and can you absolute swear, that not of your family is sucking off the government's &quot;tit&quot;?  I bet if you look honestly and hard enough, you will see I am right.  Will you ever agree with me in public. NEVER.  Case closed.  Move on to the next one in line.<br><br>
doc Spatz
